The paper deals with the problem of determining the highest rate of zero undetected-error communication over a link with adversarial noise, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the study of graph homomorphisms and the Gilbert-Varshamov bound, which are topics in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science (cs.DS, cs.CC). The use of linear programming and the Lovasz theta function suggests a connection to optimization and algorithms (cs.NI), while the consideration of communication over noisy channels may also relate to signal processing (cs.SI).
